---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DateTimeCalculatorComponent from "../components/DateTimeCalculator";

const title = "Date & Time Calculator | Duration, Add Days, Age";
const description = "Calculate duration between dates, add or subtract days, find your exact age, and count business days with our free online Date & Time Calculator.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <DateTimeCalculatorComponent client:load />

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 space-y-12 text-gray-700">
    <article class="prose prose-slate lg:prose-lg mx-auto">
      <h2>What Can You Do with a Date & Time Calculator?</h2>
      <p>
        Time is complex. Our <strong>Date & Time Calculator</strong> simplifies it by handling the math for you. Whether you're planning a project, calculating your exact age, or figuring out how many days are left until a deadline, this tool provides instant accuracy.
      </p>

      <h2>Common Use Cases</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-2">Project Planning</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Calculate the exact end date of a project by adding business days to a start date, excluding weekends.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-2">Age Calculation</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Find out exactly how many years, months, and days you've been aliveâ€”down to the second.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-2">Event Countdowns</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Know exactly how many days are left until a wedding, vacation, or retirement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-2">Time Difference</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Calculate the duration between two specific dates to track tenure, subscriptions, or historical events.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Understanding Time Concepts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Leap Years:</strong> Every 4 years (mostly), an extra day (Feb 29) is added to keep our calendar in sync with the Earth's orbit.</li>
        <li><strong>Business Days:</strong> Typically Monday through Friday, excluding public holidays. Essential for shipping and corporate deadlines.</li>
        <li><strong>Time Zones:</strong> The world is divided into 24 time zones. Calculating duration across zones requires converting to UTC first.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose space-y-4">
        <details class="group bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer">
          <summary class="font-semibold list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>Does this calculator account for leap years?</span>
            <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
            Yes, our calculator automatically detects leap years and adjusts the day count for February accordingly.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer">
          <summary class="font-semibold list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>How are months calculated?</span>
            <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
            Since months vary in length (28-31 days), we calculate the difference based on calendar months. For example, Jan 15 to Feb 15 is exactly 1 month.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer">
          <summary class="font-semibold list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>Can I calculate working days only?</span>
            <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
            Yes, use the "Business Days" mode to exclude weekends from your calculation. This is perfect for project management.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
